# Variable Configuration

File: `variables.tf`

```hcl id="1sbf5z"
# Define a single object variable to hold EC2 instance details
variable "insta_details" {
  type = object({
    vol_siz    = number # Root volume size in GB
    vol_typ    = string # Root volume type (e.g., gp3, gp2, io1)
    insta_deta = string # EC2 instance type (e.g., t3.micro, t2.small)
  })

  # Default values (can be overridden at runtime)
  default = {
    vol_siz    = 10         # Default root volume size
    vol_typ    = "gp3"      # Default root volume type
    insta_deta = "t3.micro" # Default EC2 instance type
  }
}

variable "extra_tags" {
  type = map(string)
  default = {
    #"app" = "Terraform"
  }

}
```

## Explanation

This activity uses an object variable named `insta_details` to group EC2-related configurations together.

Instead of creating multiple individual variables like:

* volume size
* volume type
* instance type

all values are grouped into a single object variable for better readability and maintainability.

The object contains:

* `vol_siz`
* `vol_typ`
* `insta_deta`

Default values are also provided, which Terraform uses when no override values are supplied.

Another variable named `extra_tags` is declared using `map(string)` datatype. This variable can be used to dynamically pass custom tags to resources.

