# terraform.tfvars Configuration

File: `terraform.tfvars`

```hcl
insta_details = {
  vol_siz    = 10
  vol_typ    = "gp2"
  insta_deta = "t3.small"
}
extra_tags = {
  Name = "Own-terra-tfvars"
}
```

## Explanation

The `terraform.tfvars` file is used to override the default values defined in `variables.tf`.

This allows infrastructure behavior to be changed without modifying the actual Terraform code.

For example:

Default values in `variables.tf`:

* `gp3`
* `t3.micro`

Overridden values in `terraform.tfvars`:

* `gp2`
* `t3.small`

Terraform automatically prioritizes values from `terraform.tfvars` over default values.

This is useful in real-world environments because:

* infrastructure becomes reusable
* environment-specific configurations remain separate
* code changes are minimized

