# EC2 Resource Configuration

File: `main.tf`

```hcl 
# Create an EC2 instance using the AMI and variable configuration
resource "aws_instance" "compute" {
  ami           = data.aws_ami.own_ami_ubuntu_IND.id
  instance_type = var.insta_details.insta_deta # Instance type from variable

  root_block_device {
    delete_on_termination = true
    volume_size           = var.insta_details.vol_siz # Volume size from variable
    volume_type           = var.insta_details.vol_typ # Volume type from variable
  }
  tags = {

  }
}
```

## Explanation

This resource creates an EC2 instance using:

* dynamically fetched Ubuntu AMI
* values supplied through Terraform variables

The AMI is referenced from the data source:

```hcl 
data.aws_ami.own_ami_ubuntu_IND.id
```

The instance type and root volume settings are dynamically fetched from the `insta_details` object variable.

The `root_block_device` block configures:

* root EBS volume size
* root EBS volume type

The parameter:

```hcl 
delete_on_termination = true
```

ensures that the EBS root volume is automatically deleted when the EC2 instance is terminated, helping avoid unnecessary storage costs.
